We first identify the key figures from the provided statements.

1. Debt to Asset Ratio  
 • Total Liabilities are given by Total Current Liabilities = 624,988.48  
 • Total Assets (end) = 15,528,390.30  
  Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets  
  = 624,988.48 / 15,528,390.30  
  ≈ 0.04

2. Gross Profit Margin  
 • Gross Profit = 2,861,769.51  
 • Total Revenue = 4,879,769.51  
  Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
  = (2,861,769.51 / 4,879,769.51) × 100%  
  ≈ 58.65%

3. Operating Cash Flow Ratio  
 • Net Cash Flow From Operating Activities = -862,455.97  
 • Total Current Liabilities = 624,988.48  
  Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities  
  = -862,455.97 / 624,988.48  
  ≈ -1.38

Thus, we have:

{

    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.04",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "58.65%",
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-1.38"
  }
